[SN]TITLE[SN]
Preston crash: Man dies after scooter collision

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A scooter rider who "lost control" of his bike while approaching a bend has died, police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Richard Bean, who was a cleaning supervisor at Preston's Fishergate Centre, collided with a row of barriers on Leyland Road at Lower Penwortham.
Lancashire Police are appealing for witnesses after the 39-year-old died at the scene.
In a tribute, his family said they were "devastated", adding he was a "loving husband, dad and grandad".
